Subject: [PATCH 243/254] gpio: Add IRQ_DOMAIN to "select" field for

Upstream: git://git.rocketboards.org/linux-socfpga.git
 GPIO_ALTERA

GPIO_ALTERA driver uses IRQ_DOMAIN to provide interrupts, thus needs to "select IRQ_DOMAIN".
This changes adds "select IRQ_DOMAIN" to the Kconfig

Signed-off-by: Tien Hock Loh <thloh@altera.com>
(cherry picked from commit b71f31cfd69c14349d670c5995e70a52f702d92e)
Signed-off-by: Zumeng Chen <zumeng.chen@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/gpio/Kconfig |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpio/Kconfig b/drivers/gpio/Kconfig
index b528fa9..3d30f0f 100644
--- a/drivers/gpio/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/gpio/Kconfig
@@ -88,6 +88,7 @@ config GPIO_GENERIC_PLATFORM
 config GPIO_ALTERA
        tristate "Altera GPIO"
        depends on OF_GPIO
+       select IRQ_DOMAIN
        help
          Say yes here to support the Altera PIO device.
 
